comments: Markkanen (UTA) legally contests Banchero's (ORL) perimeter jump shot attempt.
Fultz (ORL) legally contests Clarkson's (UTA) perimeter jump shot attempt.
Bamba (ORL) and Kessler (UTA) engage and disengage during the rebounding opportunity and the contact is marginal.
Bamba (ORL) maintains verticality and absorbs the contact that occurs during Markkanen's (UTA) driving shot attempt.
Kessler (UTA) legally contests Bamba's (ORL) layup attempt at the basket.
Clarkson (UTA) maintains his left foot as his pivot.
Fultz (ORL) moves alongside Sexton (UTA) during the drive and the contact is marginal.
Fultz (ORL) legally contests Sexton's (UTA) jump shot attempt.
Carter Jr. (ORL) establishes himself in Clarkson's (UTA) path and marginal contact occurs as Clarkson goes over the pick.
Carter Jr. (ORL) rolls into the paint and comes together with Kessler (UTA) and the contact is marginal.
Clarkson (UTA) goes into the air and marginal body contact occurs with Fultz (ORL) during Clarkson's contest of the driving shot attempt.
Fultz (ORL) aligns along Clarkson's (UTA) path and marginal body contact occurs.
Fultz (ORL) moves alongside Clarkson's (UTA) path and marginal body contact occurs during Clarkson's driving shot attempt.
Clarkson (UTA) brings the ball toward the basket and his arm brushes Fultz's (ORL) side after the gather. The contact during the driving shot attempt is marginal.
Carter Jr. (ORL) firms up on his left leg and marginal contact occurs as Beasley (UTA) fights over the screen.
Beasley (UTA) legally contests F. Wagner's (ORL) perimeter jump shot attempt.
Banchero (ORL) and Sexton (UTA) engage and disengage during the rebounding opportunity and the contact is marginal.
Banchero (ORL) commits a take foul on Sexton (UTA) in transition. The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Fultz (ORL) reaches in for the ball and steps into Sexton's (UTA) space and the ensuing body contact impacts Sexton's SQBR.
Kessler (UTA) briefly holds his forearm to Bamba's (ORL) back and marginal contact occurs during the rebounding opportunity.
Banchero (ORL) reaches for the ball and initiates contact with Kessler's (UTA) arm, which impacts his layup attempt at the basket.
Markkanen (UTA) briefly brings his hand to Ross' (ORL) side and marginal contact occurs as the screen is set.
Carter Jr. (ORL) establishes himself in Markkanen's (UTA) path and marginal contact occurs as the two players come together during the screen.
Carter Jr. (ORL) holds his arms out slightly as he establishes himself in Agbaji's (UTA) path and marginal contact occurs as they come together during the pick.
Markkanen (UTA) gets to ball height and cleanly blocks F. Wagner's (ORL) perimeter jump shot attempt.
Ross (ORL) commits a take foul on Markkanen (UTA) in transition. The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Markkanen (UTA) engages and disengages with Carter Jr. (ORL) and the contact is marginal.
Fultz (ORL) maintains legal position in-play while corralling the pass.
Kessler (UTA) legally contests Fultz's (ORL) perimeter jump shot attempt.
